25/09/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- In a speech Wednesday (24 September) at the open meeting of the UN Security Council, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy said Sofia is ready to support a new Security Council resolution aimed at enhancing the UN role in Iraq.
The effort is to reduce the impression of imposition of foreign "order" in post-war countries.
Also Wednesday, Bulgarian Deputy Foreign Minister Ivan Petkov was in Skopje meeting with his Macedonian counterpart, Fuad Hasanovic.
The two officials discussed bilateral relations and efforts by both countries to join NATO and the EU.
They also pledged to accelerate construction of Corridor 8.
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 25/09/03;
BTA, BNT, BNR, MIA - 24/09/03)
